The jiraissues macro documentation links users to http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Displaying+Search+Results+in+XML for the complete list of possible column names. This refers to two column names 'allcustom' and 'custom__xxxxx_'. Neither of those appear to apply to the jiraissues macro. If a user wants to display a custom field, they need to refer to it by its friendly configured name, not by custom+id.

Perhaps the documentation could be updated in a way that more accurately describes the correct list of column names and how you refer to custom columns (ie. no whitespace between the , or ;, the full name with spaces, etc).

